---
layout: default.njk
title: The Satsuma Diaries 🍊 — Satsuma
description: A tongue-in-cheek project changelog written by Pip, a junior intern AI keeping tabs on what's shipping in the Satsuma language project.
nav_id: diaries
permalink: diaries.html
---

<main class="pt-16 min-h-screen">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="gradient-hero py-16 border-b border-orange-light/30">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 bg-orange/10 rounded-full text-sm font-medium text-orange-dark mb-6">
          <span>🍊</span>
          <span>Written by an AI intern</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-charcoal leading-tight mb-4">
          The Satsuma Diaries
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-warm-gray leading-relaxed mb-4">
          A tongue-in-cheek project changelog written by <strong class="text-charcoal">Pip</strong>,
          a fictional junior intern AI tasked with keeping tabs on what's shipping.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-warm-gray leading-relaxed">
          Pip explains technical things in plain language and files observations about the pace of work
          and what changed in the project. If you want to know what's been happening in the Satsuma
          project without reading a raw changelog, this is your spot. None of this is serious.
          Most of it is accurate.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Diary reader -->
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-10">

    {% if diaries.length > 0 %}

    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start">

      <!-- Sidebar: entry list -->
      <aside class="w-full md:w-56 flex-shrink-0 md:sticky md:top-24">
        <nav class="diary-sidebar bg-white border border-orange-light/40 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
          <div class="px-4 py-3 border-b border-orange-light/30 bg-peach">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-warm-gray uppercase tracking-wide">Entries</p>
          </div>
          <div class="overflow-y-auto max-h-[calc(100vh-10rem)]">
            {% for group in diaries | groupByMonth %}
              <div class="px-4 pt-3 pb-1">
                <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-warm-gray/70 uppercase tracking-wide">{{ group.label }}</p>
              </div>
              {% for entry in group.entries %}
                <button
                  class="diary-entry-btn w-full text-left px-4 py-2 text-sm text-charcoal hover:bg-peach transition-colors"
                  data-path="{{ entry.contentPath }}"
                  data-date="{{ entry.date }}"
                >
                  <span class="diary-entry-date block font-medium">{{ entry.date | formatDiaryDate }}</span>
                  <span class="diary-entry-title block text-xs text-warm-gray truncate mt-0.5">{{ entry.title }}</span>
                </button>
              {% endfor %}
            {% endfor %}
          </div>
        </nav>
      </aside>

      <!-- Main content -->
      <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
        <div id="diary-loading" class="hidden py-16 text-center text-warm-gray">
          <div class="inline-block w-6 h-6 border-2 border-orange border-t-transparent rounded-full animate-spin mb-3"></div>
          <p class="text-sm">Loading entry…</p>
        </div>
        <div id="diary-error" class="hidden py-16 text-center text-warm-gray">
          <p class="text-sm">Couldn't load this entry. Pip may have misfiled it.</p>
        </div>
        <div id="diary-empty" class="py-16 text-center text-warm-gray">
          <p class="text-4xl mb-4">🍊</p>
          <p class="text-sm">Select an entry from the list to start reading.</p>
        </div>
        <article id="diary-content" class="diary-prose hidden"></article>
      </div>

    </div>

    {% else %}

    <div class="py-24 text-center text-warm-gray">
      <p class="text-4xl mb-4">🍊</p>
      <p class="text-base font-medium text-charcoal mb-2">No entries yet</p>
      <p class="text-sm">Diary entries are copied in at deploy time. Run the site locally after copying
        <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-peach px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">satsuma-diaries/</code>
        into the <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-peach px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">site/</code> directory.</p>
    </div>

    {% endif %}

  </section>

</main>

<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/marked@13/marked.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/dompurify@3/dist/purify.min.js"></script>
<script src="js/diaries.js"></script>
